commitResults.messageBody:
All the logic were in the Duke class.

Extracting the common behavior out to classes improves readability

Let's create classes to manage the UI, parsing, command logic and storage logic

commitResults.messageTitle: Organise classes into packages
commitResults.messageBody:
Classes were all in one 'Java' folder.

Packages will make the source directory neater and easier to maintain.

Let's organise the classes into 4 packages. Util, task, exception and command

Add assertions to verify any assumptions in the method
commitResults.messageBody:
Several methods make assumptions about the input without checking if they are true

Assertions could catch bugs that could be caused by these assumptions.

Assertion provide a more elegant solution to check these assumptions as compared to if-else statements.

Let's add assertions to verify the assumptions in all methods.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code class Storage to structure clearer
commitResults.messageBody:
The parsing of the save file was done inside storage class with a lot of code duplication.

An method to do the parsing would make the code more readable.

Adding a new method in the Parser class called parseSaveFileLine would abstract out this logic from the Storage class.

Let's move the logic from Storage into this new method in the Parser class
